This is simply a question of whether it is better practice to have a default value for a base class, which is overwritten with css specificity rules, or whether it&#39;s better to not ever apply the original css in cases where it is not wanted.

What is best practice? Are there consequences in terms of load times in the browser?


Example of default value, overwritten with css specificity rule:
```sass
.button {
    ...
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 1em 1.5em 1em 1.5em;
    &amp;.small {
        font-weight: 400;
        padding: 0.5em 0.75em 0.5em 0.75em;
    }
}
```
Example of only applying the css when it is intended to be used:
```sass
.button {
    ...
    &amp;:not(.small) {
        font-weight: 500;
        padding: 1em 1.5em 1em 1.5em;
    }
    &amp;.small {
        font-weight: 400;
        padding: 0.5em 0.75em 0.5em 0.75em;
    }
}
```

